<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><items termsofuse="https://boardgamegeek.com/xmlapi/termsofuse"><item type="boardgame" id="378903">
                                     				
				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="植民地資本主義 (Colonize)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;#230;&amp;#164;&amp;#141;&amp;#230;&amp;#176;&amp;#145;&amp;#229;&amp;#156;&amp;#176;&amp;#232;&amp;#179;&amp;#135;&amp;#230;&amp;#156;&amp;#172;&amp;#228;&amp;#184;&amp;#187;&amp;#231;&amp;#190;&amp;#169; (&amp;quot;Colonize&amp;quot;) is a worker placement game in which players create companies as capitalists, secure colonial interests, and gain social prestige. Players aim to win the final game by gaining victory points through their own actions.&amp;#10;The winner is the player with the most victory points at the end of three generations in the game.&amp;#10;So grab your bag of gold coins and embark on a journey to capitalize the world.&amp;#10;There are two types of cards in the game.&amp;#10;These are the &amp;quot;Corporate Card&amp;quot;, which is a workplace where workers are placed to generate funds, and the &amp;quot;Colonial Card&amp;quot;, which produces a Colony Concession Icon that strengthens the effect of the Company Card and is a condition for goals.&amp;#10;The basic game flow is that the player pays the cost on the upper left of the card on his turn, purchases the card from the market, demonstrates its effect, and moves to the next player's turn.&amp;#10;The number of yellow shields drawn on the card is the &amp;quot;victory point&amp;quot;, and the player who finally got the most of this is the winner.&amp;#10;You can also get victory points for achieving various &amp;quot;goal cards&amp;quot; and the majority of each icon, which will annoy the player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
